ilic substitution/addition reaction.\n\nThe most precise mechanistic classification would be \"nucleophilic addition\" since we're adding a nucleophile to a carbocation (no leaving group is displaced from C:20).\n\nActually, looking more carefully - the carbocation is already formed (CH+:20), so the nucleophile attacks the electrophilic carbon. This is nucleophilic addition to a carbocation.\n\nMechanistic class: nucleophilic_addition\nReaction center: N:10-C:20 bond formation (nucleophilic attack of pyridine N on benzylic cation)"
